olive oil
1 courgette
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
¼ tsp salt
1 onion
½ tbs water
1 tsp brown sugar
2 pizza bases
1 sachet pizza sauce
1 pear
1 bag salad leaves
1 tbs balsamic vinegar (for the onion)
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
½ tbs balsamic vinegar (for the salad)
½ packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Thinly slice courgette into rounds.
• Place courgette, peeled & chopped pumpkin, salt and a drizzle of olive oil on a lined oven tray. Season with pepper. Toss to coat, then spread in a single layer. Roast until just tender, 15-20 minutes.

• While the veggies are roasting, thinly slice red onion.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium heat. Cook onion, stirring, until softened, 5-6 minutes. Add balsamic vinegar (for the onion), water and brown sugar and mix well. Cook until dark and sticky, 3-5 minutes.

• Lay pizza bases on a flat surface, rough side down. Spread pizza sauceevenly across the bases using the back of a spoon.
• Top pizzas evenly with roasted pumpkin, courgette and caramelised onion. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Bake pizzas directly on wire oven racks until cheese is melted and golden, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: Placing the pizzas directly onto the wire racks helps the base to crisp up.

• While pizzas are baking, thinly slice pear.
• In a medium bowl, combine pear, spinach & rocket mix, balsamic vinegar(for the salad) and a drizzle of olive oil. Toss to coat and season.
• Crumble Greek salad cheese/feta cheese (see ingredients) over the pizzas. Cut pizzas into slices and divide between plates.
• Serve with pear salad.

TIP: Garnish your pizzas with a little of the salad if you like!